unit.name: 2 Infantry Division HQ
unit.History: The 2nd "Indianhead" Division landed in Normandy on June 8. By December, it had been in action almost continuously and was considered one of the best infantry divisions in the ETO. On December 16th, two of its three infantry regiments were engaged in an offensive operation at Wahlerscheid crossroads, about 8 km northwest of Rocherath (off map)

commander.Name: Walter M. Robertson
commander.PersBio: Walter Melville Robertson was born on June 15th, 1888 in Virginia. Robertson's cool leadership and organizational skills was instrumental in winning the battle of Rocherath and Krinkelt. He was awarded the DSC and Bronze Star for his performance on December 17th.
commander.Title: CO
